<TITLE> Court grants bail to BNP leader Aman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 21 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court on Wedenesday granted bail to former BNP state minister Amanullah Aman in an attempted murder case. Metropolitan judge A N M Bashirullah issued the bail order. On Oct 12, additional chief metropolitan magistrate Mohammed Ehsanul Haque had refused him bail. The case involving an armed attack on businessman Osman Gani was filed by the victim's brother, Abdul Mannaf, with Mohammadpur police in the capital on May 31 this year. One of the accused gunmen in the case, Ataur Rahman, in a confessional statement said he and others had acted on Aman's order and shot Gani. Aman was arrested at Zia International Airport as he returned from medical treatment abroad on Sept 30. Gani, a BNP activist and a businessman from Aman's parliamentary constituency in Keraniganj, earlier told bdnews24.com that he had been refused nomination by BNP for Keraniganj constituency. Aman who contested as the BNP candidate later pressed Gani to work for him. As gain refused to do so, Aman sent terrorists to kill Gani on May 29. The case details, seen by bdnews24.com senior legal affairs correspondent, say Gani and his friend Abdus Sobhan were in a car at Mohammadpur in the capital on May 29 when gunmen stopped their car near Salimullah Road and opened fire. Gani, it was alleged, took five bullets in his body. The detectives had arrested five suspects named Sohel Rana, Alamgir Hossain, Ebadul Islam Badol, G M Morshed Tutul and Ataur Rahman. Asaduzzaman, additional deputy commissioner of DB police, said all five named Aman as the mastermind of the attempted murder. 
